1. Veštice su uvek bile okarakterisane kao zle u narodnim pričama. (*Veštice*, subject, plural) (Witches have always been characterized as evil in folk tales.)
2. Ova knjiga govori o različitim vrstama veštica koje su postojale u prošlosti. (*veštica*, object, singular) (This book talks about different types of witches that existed in the past.)
3. Rekli su joj da se ne igra sa vešticama, ali nije ih poslušala. (*vešticama*, object, plural) (They told her not to play with witches, but she didn't listen.)
4. Sumnjam da su veštice stvarne, to su samo priče za decu. (*veštice*, subject, plural) (I doubt that witches are real, they're just stories for children.)
5. Ove godine ćemo se maskirati kao veštice za Noć veštica. (*veštice*, object, plural) (This year we'll dress up as witches for Halloween.)
6. Veštice su imale moć da čine zle stvari ljudima. (*veštice*, subject, plural) (Witches had the power to do evil things to people.)
7. Svi su bili uplašeni od veštica i smatrali su da donose nesreću. (*veštica*, object, singular) (Everyone was afraid of witches and believed they brought bad luck.)
8. U toj kući su živele veštice koje su zastrašivale ljude iz okoline. (*veštice*, subject, plural) (Witches lived in that house and scared people from the surrounding area.)
9. Kada su veštice plesale, činilo se kao da lebde iznad tla. (*veštice*, subject, plural) (When witches danced, it seemed like they were floating above the ground.)
10. Veštica je prokletstvo koje je bačeno na tu porodicu. (*veštica*, subject, singular) (A witch is a curse that was cast upon that family.)